Package de.hshn.mi.pdbg.basicservice.gui.model

Class WardModel.WardWrapper

java.lang.Object
de.hshn.mi.pdbg.basicservice.gui.model.WardModel.WardWrapper
Enclosing class:
WardModel
public class WardModel.WardWrapper extends Object
A class encapsulating a currently valid Ward instance, and a previously valid instance representing the same Ward. In this way it is possible to match different instances of the same database tuple, especially persistent and respective non-persistent ones, where the ID cannot be used for matching (as the non-persistent instance has the PersistentObject.INVALID_OBJECT_ID set). The class also contains a boolean as a flag for whether the encapsulated instance has been changed since the last time being persisted. This flag can be used for data presentation issues (e.g. different coloring) and optimizing the persisting of whole lists of objects.
Author:
Simon Pezold

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object object)
      Two wrappers are considered equal if the given parameter is valid and if at least one of the following conditions applies:
      • the wrappers are identical instances
      • a contained instance in one wrapper is identical to a contained instance in the other wrapper while at least one of the currently compared contained instances is not null (thus avoiding true for null == null)
      • both contained "current" instances are persistent and have identical objectIDs
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      object - must not be null, must be an instance of the same wrapper class
      Returns:
      true if the stated conditions apply, else false
